{{>header}}

<body>
  {{>navbar}}


  <!-- Main Page -->
  <div class="container p-5 bg-light">
    <div class="container mb-4 text-dark">
      <h1 class="text-success">{{title}}</h1>
      <h5 class="lh-base" style="font-weight:300">Browse the history of nursing in Saskatchewan and Alberta by timeline.
      </h5>
    </div>

    <div class="container">
      <div class="row justify-content-md-center">
        {{!-- Pre 1900s --}}
        <div class="col-md-auto" style="width:25rem">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">Pre 1900's</h5>
              <p class="card-text">Travel to pre-1900 Alberta, where nurses led groundbreaking innovations. Inspired by
                Florence Nightingale, they pioneered transformative changes in healthcare, shaping a future of
                excellence in nursing and healthcare across the region.</p>
              <br>
              <a href="/timeline/pre1900" class="btn bg-success text-light">View</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        {{!-- 1900 --}}
        <div class="col-md-auto" style="width:25rem">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">1900's</h5>
              <p class="card-text">In 1900s, Medicine Hat General Hospital became the first regular hospital in "the
                territories," revolutionizing healthcare access. Meanwhile, in Saskatoon, Sisters Guay and Phaneuf at
                St. Paul's Hospital pioneered medical care and innovation, shaping Saskatchewan's medical landscape.</p>
              <a href="/timeline/1900" class="btn bg-success text-light">View</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        {{!-- 1910 --}}
        <div class="col-md-auto" style="width:25rem">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">1910's</h5>
              <p class="card-text">Step into the pivotal year of 1910, where Alberta nurses bravely ventured into the
                "Great War," displaying unwavering dedication. Amidst the chaos, the specter of the Spanish influenza
                cast a heavy shadow, showcasing the resilience and commitment of healthcare heroes in challenging times.
              </p>
              <a href="/timeline/1910" class="btn bg-success text-light">View</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row justify-content-md-center mt-3">

        {{!-- 1920 --}}
        <div class="col-md-auto" style="width:25rem">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">1920's</h5>
              <p class="card-text">Time marked in 1920 by bold changes and cultural shifts.
                Meet Kate Brightly, a trailblazing figure who captured attention with her daring "bob" hairstyle,
                symbolizing the spirit of independence and liberation that defined the era.</p>
              <a href="/timeline/1920" class="btn bg-success text-light">View</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        {{!-- 1930 --}}
        <div class="col-md-auto" style="width:25rem">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">1930's</h5>
              <p class="card-text">Journey to the 1930s, where the Great Depression shaped nursing. Despite challenges,
                Kathleen Ellis established a pioneering nurses' college, reflecting nurses' resilience in providing
                crucial care during tough times.</p>
              <a href="/timeline/1930" class="btn bg-success text-light">View</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        {{!-- 1940 --}}
        <div class="col-md-auto" style="width:25rem">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">1940's</h5>
              <p class="card-text"> In the 1940s, healthcare milestones and exceptional individuals define the era. Agnes MacLeod's leadership in wartime healthcare showcases bravery, while the introduction of air ambulance services revolutionizes emergency response.</p>
              <a href="/timeline/1940" class="btn bg-success text-light">View</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row justify-content-md-center mt-3">
      {{!-- 1950 --}}
        <div class="col-md-auto" style="width:25rem">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">1950's</h5>
              <p class="card-text">In the 1950s, nurses played a vital role in fighting polio and caring for affected
                communities. Training courses for nursing housekeepers emphasized clean healthcare environments, while
                psychiatric nursing gained recognition, reflecting a growing understanding of mental health needs.</p>
              <a href="/timeline/1950" class="btn bg-success text-light">View</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      {{!-- 1960 --}}
        <div class="col-md-auto" style="width:25rem">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">1960's</h5>
              <p class="card-text">During the 1960s, Sophie Ann Kettleson's dedication to nursing inspired countless
                others, fostering pride and commitment among nurses nationwide. Furthermore, the introduction of
                Medicare significantly influenced healthcare policies, enhancing access to vital services for millions.
              </p>
              <a href="/timeline/1960" class="btn bg-success text-light">View</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

      {{!-- 1970 --}}
        <div class="col-md-auto" style="width:25rem">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">1970's</h5>
              <p class="card-text">In the 1970s, the birth of the United Nurses of Alberta (UNA) brought about immediate
                challenges as it faced a bargaining crisis right from the start. In Saskatchewan, collective bargaining
                was introduced, paving the way for the formation of the Saskatchewan Union of Nurses.</p>
              <a href="/timeline/1970" class="btn bg-success text-light">View</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="row justify-content-md-center mt-3">
      {{!-- 1980 --}}
        <div class="col-md-auto" style="width:25rem">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">1980's</h5>
              <p class="card-text">In the 1980s, Heather Smith led nurses in advocating for patient care. Their first
                major strike in 1980 highlighted their commitment to improving working conditions and patient care
                standards. Despite challenges, nurses persisted in pushing for healthcare system improvements,
                prioritizing the well-being of patients and healthcare professionals.</p>
              <a href="/timeline/1980" class="btn bg-success text-light">View</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      {{!-- 1990 --}}
        <div class="col-md-auto" style="width:25rem">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">1990's</h5>
              <p class="card-text">During the 1990s, nursing negotiations advanced, signifying a dynamic era. Nurses
                provided key insights on health reform in the early '90s, shaping ongoing conversations. The decade also witnessed widespread nurse layoffs, presenting significant challenges amidst evolving
                healthcare environments.</p>
                <br>
              <a href="/timeline/1990" class="btn bg-success text-light">View</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      {{!-- 2000 --}}
        <div class="col-md-auto" style="width:25rem">
          <div class="card">
            <div class="card-body">
              <h5 class="card-title">2000's</h5>
              <p class="card-text">In the 2000s, nursing saw significant advances like "nursing by phone," changing how
                care is delivered. There was also a focus on Aboriginal nursing, addressing unique healthcare needs.
                Moreover, more men joined the profession, reflecting its growing diversity.</p>
                <br>
                <br>
              <a href="/timeline/2000" class="btn bg-success text-light">View</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

  </div>
  {{>footer}}

